CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 12, 1962, pg. A10, reads: "POTENTIAL SECRETARIES - The ambitious trio represents approximately 18 or more high school seniors competing for the title of "Best Potential Secretary" in a contest sponsored by the Urban League of Pittsburgh. Left to right: Patricia Miles, Elaine Bolton and Beatrice Beasley, all of Westinghouse High School. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of three young women competing in "Best Potential Secretary" contest, left to right: Patricia Miles, Elaine Bolton, and Beatrice Beasley on typewriter, in office with textured glass partitions
